OL,3,CAbuse survivors encouraged to come
OL,4,Cforward before compensation deadline
OL,6,FThese were children who had suffered
OL,7,Fin church and state run facilities
OL,8,Fbetween 1922 and 1995.
OL,10,FThe apology followed a public inquiry
OL,11,Fand the establishment of a
OL,12,Fcompensation scheme.
OL,14,FApplications for that close on the 2nd
OL,15,Fof April but campaigners for survivors
OL,16,Fsay more time is needed.
OL,18,FSandra Peake of the Wave Trauma Centre
OL,19,Fin Belfast believes the information
OL,20,Fchannels should have been greater.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/5
