OL,3,CAbuse survivors encouraged to come
OL,4,Cforward before compensation deadline
OL,6,F"There needs to be an emphasis that
OL,7,Fthis is open, this available, time is
OL,8,Fbecoming very tight in relation to
OL,9,Fmaking an application, but if there's
OL,10,Fanything government can do to look at
OL,11,Fthat deadline, they should do it,"
OL,12,Fsaid Ms Peake.
OL,14,FMarie Therese Rogers-Moloney spent the
OL,15,Ffirst part of her life in Nazareth
OL,16,Fhouse, where she was beaten and
OL,17,Fbullied by nuns.
OL,19,FShe believes there are still people
OL,20,Fout there living in silence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/5
